        <h2 class={`pt-4 text-3xl xl:text-4xl font-bold ${VARIANT_MAPS["roll"].h1}`}>Roll</h2>
        <h3 class={`pb-4 text-xl xl:text-2xl font-bold ${VARIANT_MAPS["roll"].h2}`}>Setting the stage</h3>
        <div class="pb-8 grid gap-4 xs:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
            <p class="font-bold text-xl">Before we get into the case study, let's give some context. Roll by ADP's ethos is to rethink how businesses run payroll & <abbr title="Human Capital Management">HCM</abbr>. At the heart of Roll is an event engine that captures state changes with an event object, stored in sequence and we apply this to a few interfaces on mobile devices and desktop.</p>
            <p class="text-xl"> Roll at it's core is a self service app that allows business owners to run payroll and manage <abbr title="Human Capital Management">HCM</abbr> through a chat bot with a sophisticated suite of <abbr title="Machine Learning">ML</abbr> algorithms and <abbr title="Artificial Intelligence">AI</abbr>. Business owners, our clients, need to run payroll on the go. In this case study I'll be walking you through how I overcame the business challenges to get a clear and concise design solution for a manager managing employee's hours.</p>
            <p class="text-xl">There are a sea of attributes that can be applied to a manager or employee and they can be mixed and matched depending on the company, location and organization structure. What type of payment method are we using? What's the employees gross income this period? Did they get a mid-cycle rise? How many hours did they work? Did they have overtime or sick time?</p>
        </div>
