            <p class="lg:text-xl b-4">I start to see how an accordion design pattern could solve this. I proceed to draw out an example on the whiteboard explaining how an accordion works, and how it can solve the business problem. This affords us the ability to hide attributes that are less common like overtime, payment type, etc.. Everyone is in agreement. Now, we sit and talk about the hierarchy of the main attributes. Marking the whiteboard I am articulating aloud font size, weight, color and placement. More than that, I'm educating the team so they can understand the importance of this visual hierarchy. I'm also pressing them on being judicious about what becomes a main attribute to keep down the potential for cognitive overload. Finally we have a wireframe everyone is happy with. Before I move to building high fidelity mockups we discuss a few more use business cases where we'll need to use this new design pattern. It passes the pressure test. Now I am tasked with coming up with some higher fidelity mockups with real data that we can use to discuss the visual hierarchy in more detail.</p>
