        <div class="md:row-span-3">
            <p class="lg:text-xl">When designing high fidelity mockups I always work with real information. We need to consider edge cases and it helps to push the design limits with real names, numbers and data. Hopping into <code>&mdash; fill in design application of the week &mdash;</code> I layout the accordion panels, closed at first. I design an area to signal to users that there is 'more' they can do using a chevron and text, then I get to laying out the main attributes. As I make progress I am talking to the backend developers clarifying data structures and thinking about how I'll be able to make these panel layouts pliable with flexbox. Workin with the SME's I'm really looking for ways to break this design. How any decimal places will we encounter? What are the different pay cycles? What will we do when we're out of room when translated to German? I try a few layout variations that push the design out of the existing design system for exploration. I consider color, contrast ratios font size for readability and accessibility. Moving to the secound round of mockups I bring in the supplementary attributes on the expanded panel portion of the accordion. We strip out any unnecessary design elements that do not serve a purpose. This keeps the user on task, focused.</p>
